Common Controller

Base URL: /api

Endpoint: Get CSRF Token
URL: /api/getCsrfToken
Method: GET

Description:
This endpoint is used to retrieve a CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery) token for securing HTTP requests. The token is
automatically generated by Spring Security and will be included in the response headers.

Request Headers:
No specific headers are required for this endpoint.

Query Parameters:
None.

Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Headers:
The CSRF token will be provided in the response headers, typically under the header name X-CSRF-TOKEN.
